CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1773748973
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FWhat is meningitis and who can it
OL,7,Faffect?
OL,9,FMeningitis is inflammation of the
OL,10,Fmembranes that surround the brain and
OL,11,Fspinal cord. It can be caused by
OL,12,Fviruses or bacteria, but the most
OL,13,Fserious cases are often caused by the
OL,14,Fbacterium Neisseria meningitidis.
OL,16,FAnyone can get meningitis, but it is
OL,17,Fmost commonly caught by babies, young
OL,18,Fchildren, teenagers and young adults.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1773748973
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FThis is due in part to people in this
OL,7,Fage group carrying the bacteria in the
OL,8,Fnose or throat without symptoms.
OL,10,FThe bacteria that cause meningococcal
OL,11,Fmeningitis are often carried
OL,12,Fharmlessly in the nose and throat;
OL,13,Faround 10% of the general population
OL,14,Fcarries them without ever becoming
OL,15,Fill. In adolescents and young adults,
OL,16,Fcarriage can be higher, with large UK
OL,17,Fstudies showing rates between 7% and
OL,18,F18%.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1773748973
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FTransmission requires close, prolonged
OL,7,Fcontact such as coughing, sneezing or
OL,8,Fkissing, and even among carriers only
OL,9,Fa very small proportion ever develops
OL,10,Finvasive disease.
OL,12,FOutbreaks usually happen when a
OL,13,Fparticular meningococcal strain enters
OL,14,Fa community where people are mixing
OL,15,Fclosely, such as a university, which
OL,16,Fcreates an environment where the
OL,17,Fbacteria can spread more easily.
OL,19,FWhat are the symptoms of meningitis?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1773748974
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FSymptoms of meningitis can look
OL,7,Fsimilar to common illnesses like a
OL,8,Fcold or flu, however, someone with
OL,9,Fmeningitis will usually become
OL,10,Fseriously ill in a matter of hours.
OL,12,FSymptoms can include fever, seizures,
OL,13,Fvomiting, headache, a stiff neck, or a
OL,14,Frash that does not fade when a glass
OL,15,Fis pressed against it.
OL,17,FSome people may also become drowsy,
OL,18,Funresponsive or sensitive to bright
OL,19,Flights.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1773748974
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FSymptoms can appear in any order and
OL,7,Fmay not always be present at once.
OL,9,FThe UK Health Security Agency advises
OL,10,Fcalling 999 immediately or going to
OL,11,Fyour nearest A&E if you think you or
OL,12,Fsomeone in your care could have
OL,13,Fmeningitis or septicaemia, as people
OL,14,Fcan become unwell very quickly.
OL,16,FYou can call NHS 111 if you're unsure
OL,17,Fwhether it's serious.
OL,19,FWhat causes meningitis and how does it
OL,20,Fspread?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30408
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1773748974
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FIn most cases, meningitis is caused by
OL,7,Fa viral or bacterial infection. Viral
OL,8,Fmeningitis is more common and
OL,9,Ftypically less serious, often getting
OL,10,Fbetter within 7 to 10 days.
OL,12,FMeanwhile, bacterial meningitis is
OL,13,Frare but can be life-threatening.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30409
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1773748974
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FDr Zina Alfahl, School of Medicine,
OL,7,FUniversity of Galway, says outbreaks
OL,8,Fare usually driven by a combination of
OL,9,Ffactors, "the characteristics of the
OL,10,Fstrain itself, the level of immunity
OL,11,Fin the population, and environmental
OL,12,Ffactors like crowded living or social
OL,13,Fsettings where people mix intensively".
OL,15,FUsually, the meningitis is spread by
OL,16,Fpeople who are not ill themselves, but
OL,17,Frather carry the viruses or bacteria
OL,18,Fin their nose or throat.
OL,20,FIn some cases, it can be spread by
OL,21,Fsomeone with meningitis.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30410
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1773748974
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FThe UKHSA says that "very
OL,7,Foccasionally" meningococcal bacteria
OL,8,Fcan cause serious illness, including
OL,9,Finflammation of the lining of the
OL,10,Fbrain and blood poisoning, which can
OL,11,Frapidly lead to sepsis.
OL,13,FWhat can people do to protect
OL,14,Fthemselves from meningitis?
OL,16,FDr Alfahl says that the most
OL,17,F"important thing is recognising
OL,18,Fsymptoms early and seeking medical
OL,19,Fhelp quickly".
OL,26,@nD@UOUoD@MO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30411
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1773748974
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FEarly symptoms can look like flu but
OL,7,Fpeople should seek urgent medical
OL,8,Fadvice if symptoms worsen or if there
OL,9,Fare warning signs such as neck
OL,10,Fstiffness, confusion, sensitivity to
OL,11,Flight, or a rash that doesn't fade
OL,12,Fwhen pressed.
OL,14,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,15,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,16,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,17,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,19,FIs there a vaccine for meningitis, and
OL,20,Fhow do I know if I've had one?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30412
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1773748974
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FSeveral vaccines protect against
OL,7,Fdifferent meningococcal groups,
OL,8,Fincluding MenB and MenACWY. Other
OL,9,Froutine childhood vaccines, such as
OL,10,Fthe 6-in-1 vaccine and MMR, protect
OL,11,Fagainst infections that can also cause
OL,12,Fmeningitis.
OL,14,FThe pneumococcal vaccine is offered to
OL,15,Fbabies in two doses or a single dose
OL,16,Fto adults aged 65 or over.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30413
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1773748974
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FTeenagers, sixth formers and freshers
OL,7,Fattending university for the first
OL,8,Ftime can have the MenACWY vaccine,
OL,9,Fwhich can help protect against
OL,10,Fmeningitis and sepsis.
OL,12,F"Vaccination remains the best
OL,13,Fprotection. The MenACWY and MenB
OL,14,Fvaccines used in the UK are safe,
OL,15,Fwelltested, and available free to
OL,16,Feligible UK and international
OL,17,Fstudents," said Dr Simon Clarke,
OL,18,FAssociate Professor of Cellular
OL,19,FMicrobiology, University of Reading.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30414
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1773748974
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FThe MenACWY vaccine can be given up to
OL,7,Fthe age of 25 if it has been missed
OL,8,Fand is also available to some
OL,9,Findividuals who are at greater risk
OL,10,Fdue to a medical condition, work,
OL,11,Ftravel or close contact with someone
OL,12,Fwho is infected.
OL,14,FIf you are unsure if you or your child
OL,15,Fhas been vaccinated, you can speak to
OL,16,Fyour GP.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G14/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30415
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1773748974
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FWhile the NHS offers vaccinations to
OL,7,Fthose most at risk, private
OL,8,Fvaccinations are available at some
OL,9,Ftravel clinics, private GP practices
OL,10,Fand pharmacies.
OL,12,FDr Alfahl said the meningococcal
OL,13,Fvaccines used in the UK are "highly
OL,14,Feffective, particularly the MenACWY
OL,15,Fvaccine given to teenagers".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G15/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30416
SC,0016
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1773748974
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,F"Uptake in adolescents is generally
OL,7,Fgood ` around 70`75% in recent school
OL,8,Fcohorts ` although it hasn't fully
OL,9,Freturned to pre-pandemic levels...
OL,10,FHowever, many current university
OL,11,Fstudents were born before the infant
OL,12,FMenB programme began in 2015, which
OL,13,Fmeans some of them may never have been
OL,14,Froutinely offered that vaccine."
OL,16,FWhat other ways can I help protect
OL,17,Fmyself from meningitis?
OL,19,FIt is a good habit to practice
OL,20,Fhandwashing hygiene, washing your
OL,21,Fhands after coughing or sneezing.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G16/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30417
SC,0017
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1773748974
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FYou can also avoid sharing items which
OL,7,Fcome into contact with your mouth,
OL,8,Fsuch as food, drink and eating
OL,9,Futensils.
OL,11,FRegularly cleaning surfaces can also
OL,12,Fhelp reduce the spread of germs.
OL,14,FWhat measures are being taken in Kent?
OL,16,FThe UK Health Security Agency and the
OL,17,FNHS are now arranging antibiotics for
OL,18,Fsome students at the University of
OL,19,FKent, following the outbreak there.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G17/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30418
SC,0018
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1773748974
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FTrish Mannes, UKHSA regional deputy
OL,7,Fdirector for the South East, said:
OL,8,F"Students and staff will
OL,9,Funderstandably be feeling worried
OL,10,Fabout the risk of further cases;
OL,11,Fhowever, we would like to reassure
OL,12,Fthem that close contacts of cases have
OL,13,Fbeen given antibiotics as a
OL,14,Fprecautionary measure."
OL,16,FYou can read more about the advice
OL,17,Fissued to University of Kent students
OL,18,Fhere.
OL,20,FHow is meningitis treated?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G18/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30419
SC,0019
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1773748974
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FPeople with suspected meningitis may
OL,7,Fhave to have hospital tests to get a
OL,8,Fdiagnosis and find out if their
OL,9,Fillness is a viral or bacterial
OL,10,Finfection.
OL,12,FBacterial meningitis usually requires
OL,13,Fhospital treatment for at least a
OL,14,Fweek, including antibiotics, fluids
OL,15,Fand oxygen.
OL,17,FShould students be especially careful?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G19/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30420
SC,0020
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1773748974
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FAccess to vaccinations has meant
OL,7,Foutbreaks are more unusual; however,
OL,8,Fmeningitis can spread rapidly in
OL,9,Fplaces like universities and colleges.
OL,11,FTom Nutt, chief executive of
OL,12,FMeningitis Now, says: "University
OL,13,Fstudents and young adults are among
OL,14,Fthe groups at increased risk because
OL,15,Fmeningitis bacteria can spread more
OL,16,Feasily in settings where people live,
OL,17,Fstudy and socialise closely together."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G20/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30421
SC,0021
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1773748974
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FTrish Mannes, UKHSA regional deputy
OL,7,Fdirector for the South East, adds:
OL,8,F"Students are particularly at risk of
OL,9,Fmissing the early warning signs of
OL,10,Fmeningitis because they can be easily
OL,11,Fconfused with other illnesses such as
OL,12,Fa bad cold, flu or even a hangover.
OL,14,F"That's why it's vital that, if a
OL,15,Ffriend goes to bed unwell, you check
OL,16,Fon them regularly and don't hesitate
OL,17,Fto seek medical help by contacting
OL,18,Ftheir GP or calling NHS 111 if they
OL,19,Fhave these symptoms or you're
OL,20,Fconcerned about them. This could save
OL,21,Ftheir life."
OL,26,@pD@AOUvD@AOU}D@LO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G21/22
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30422
SC,0022
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1773748974
OL,3,CMeningitis: What can people do to
OL,4,Cprotect themselves?
OL,6,FNHS advice to students is to make sure
OL,7,Ftheir vaccinations are up to date
OL,8,Fbefore starting university or college,
